<% content_for(:title, "Ruby Embassy") %>

<section class="pb-32">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-8">
    <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-hero leading-tight font-medium text-center text-navy mb-4">
      <span class="md:block leading-tight">
        Welcome to Ruby Embassy
      </span>
    </h1>

    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray space-y-8">
      <p>
        This page is a template demo. The navbar, footer, colors, typography, and layout match the main Blue Ridge Ruby website so the transition between sites is seamless.
      </p>

      <p>
        Replace this content with real pages. Use the same structural pattern — <code>section.pb-32</code> wrapping <code>div.max-w-5xl.mx-auto.px-8</code> wrapping your <code>h1</code> and a <code>div.max-w-2xl.mx-auto</code> for body prose.
      </p>

      <hr>

      <h3 class="text-section font-medium text-center mb-12 text-navy">
        How it works
      </h3>

      <p>
        The layout shell (navbar + footer) lives in the Rails application layout and wraps every page automatically. The mobile menu uses a generic toggle Stimulus controller — tap the hamburger on a narrow screen to try it.
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2">
        <li>Navbar partial: <code>app/views/shared/_navbar.html.erb</code></li>
        <li>Footer partial: <code>app/views/shared/_footer.html.erb</code></li>
        <li>Styles: <code>app/assets/stylesheets/application.css</code></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
